<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>play a love game • play for love</xh5><p> <i>play a love game—</i>said when smb.’s attitude to matters of love is not serious enough: She is afraid that you’re <u>playing a love game</u> instead of being serious.</p><p> <i>play for love</i>—(also: play for fun) play cards, etc. without stakes: The Parson did not like card games played for money, but he was willing to <u>play for love</u>.</p><p> <i>See also: love game / love play.</i></p> </entry>
